                            <comment id="13939922" author="sushanth" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2014 22:51:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;(Attaching addendum patch that was uploaded to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HCATALOG-621&quot; title=&quot;bin/hcat should include hbase jar and dependencies in the classpath&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HCATALOG-621&quot;&gt;HCATALOG-621&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13939932" author="sushanth" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2014 23:00:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ndimiduk&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ndimiduk&quot;&gt;ndimiduk&lt;/a&gt;, I created this hive jira since I was not able to respond on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HCATALOG-621&quot; title=&quot;bin/hcat should include hbase jar and dependencies in the classpath&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HCATALOG-621&quot;&gt;HCATALOG-621&lt;/a&gt;, since that seems like it&apos;s been locked down.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;+1 to the change, I&apos;ll go ahead and commit it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve experimented with both versions of the find command, and both work for me (with and without quotes, and in fact, I&apos;m more used to the backslash notation). I&apos;m using findutils-4.4.2-6.el6.x86_64. The main difference though, was that our offending jar is libthrift&amp;#42;jar, not thrift&amp;#42;jar.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13939974" author="sushanth" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2014 23:44:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed. Thanks, Nick!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13939986" author="ndimiduk" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2014 23:53:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sushanth&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sushanth&quot;&gt;sushanth&lt;/a&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
